The paper focuses on using artificial and computational intelligence-based approaches to predict potential credit default accounts. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with fraud and risk assessment, which falls under the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The paper also involves handling large amounts of data, which is a common theme in the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with financial transactions, which could be classified under the sub-category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
